  "text": "As described elsewhere in more detail, [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] optimized VBM analysis involves the following preprocessing of each subject's brain image (explained in detail in the following sections): (1) brain extraction (removal of nonbrain tissue, such as skull and dura); (2) segmentation (ie, separation of brain tissue into white matter, gray matter, and cerebrospinal fluid); (3) spatial transformation (transformation of tissue maps to common stereotaxic space); and (4) modulation (volume preservation that corrects for unintended changes in total tissue volume produced by spatial transformation).",
